    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Bronze drum-shaped vessels, often elaborately decorated with relief or free-standing animal figures, fashioned to contain cowrie-shell money in the ancient Dian kingdom of southwestern China.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
